      "content": "Your symptoms could indeed be due to muscle strain from your long flight, especially if you have a history of experiencing similar sensations after prolonged sitting. However, it's important to listen to your body and not dismiss any unusual pain. To alleviate the discomfort, try gentle stretching exercises for your chest and back, and consider applying a warm compress to the affected area. If the pain persists or worsens, it's best to seek medical attention, even if you're reluctant to visit a hospital. Your health is paramount, and a professional evaluation can help rule out any serious conditions. Remember, it's always better to be safe than sorry.",
